<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The sequence of fractions appears to rise and fall alternately. This observation can be confirmed by reference to the equation</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="//s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=F_%7Bn%2B1%7D%5E2+-+F_nF_%7Bn%2B2%7D+%3D+%28-1%29%5En&#038;bg=ffffff&#038;fg=000&#038;s=0" alt="F_{n+1}^2 - F_nF_{n+2} = (-1)^n" title="F_{n+1}^2 - F_nF_{n+2} = (-1)^n" class="latex" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>which, when divided by <img src="//s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=F_%7Bn%2B1%7DF_n&#038;bg=ffffff&#038;fg=000&#038;s=0" alt="F_{n+1}F_n" title="F_{n+1}F_n" class="latex" /> gives</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="//s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdfrac%7BF_%7Bn%2B1%7D%7D%7BF_n%7D+-+%5Cdfrac+%7BF_%7Bn%2B2%7D%7D%7BF_%7Bn%2B1%7D%7D+%3D+%5Cdfrac+%7B%28-1%29%5En%7D%7BF_%7Bn%2B1%7DF_n+%7D+%5C+%2C+&#038;bg=ffffff&#038;fg=000&#038;s=0" alt="&#92;dfrac{F_{n+1}}{F_n} - &#92;dfrac {F_{n+2}}{F_{n+1}} = &#92;dfrac {(-1)^n}{F_{n+1}F_n } &#92; , " title="&#92;dfrac{F_{n+1}}{F_n} - &#92;dfrac {F_{n+2}}{F_{n+1}} = &#92;dfrac {(-1)^n}{F_{n+1}F_n } &#92; , " class="latex" /></p>
