<p>from which we have</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="//s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cdfrac+%7BF_%7Bn%2B1%7D%7D%7BF_n%7D+%3D+%5Cdfrac+%7B%5CBig%28%5Cdfrac%7B1%2B%5Csqrt+5%7D2+%5CBig%29%5E%7Bn%2B1%7D+-+%5CBig%28%5Cdfrac%7B1-%5Csqrt+5%7D2+%5CBig%29%5E%7Bn%2B1%7D%7D+%7B%5CBig%28%5Cdfrac%7B1%2B%5Csqrt+5%7D2+%5CBig%29%5En+-+%5CBig%28%5Cdfrac%7B1-%5Csqrt+5%7D2+%5CBig%29%5En%7D&#038;bg=ffffff&#038;fg=000&#038;s=0" alt="&#92;dfrac {F_{n+1}}{F_n} = &#92;dfrac {&#92;Big(&#92;dfrac{1+&#92;sqrt 5}2 &#92;Big)^{n+1} - &#92;Big(&#92;dfrac{1-&#92;sqrt 5}2 &#92;Big)^{n+1}} {&#92;Big(&#92;dfrac{1+&#92;sqrt 5}2 &#92;Big)^n - &#92;Big(&#92;dfrac{1-&#92;sqrt 5}2 &#92;Big)^n}" title="&#92;dfrac {F_{n+1}}{F_n} = &#92;dfrac {&#92;Big(&#92;dfrac{1+&#92;sqrt 5}2 &#92;Big)^{n+1} - &#92;Big(&#92;dfrac{1-&#92;sqrt 5}2 &#92;Big)^{n+1}} {&#92;Big(&#92;dfrac{1+&#92;sqrt 5}2 &#92;Big)^n - &#92;Big(&#92;dfrac{1-&#92;sqrt 5}2 &#92;Big)^n}" class="latex" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Now look at the second terms in the numerator and denominator.</p>
<p>Since</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="//s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=-1%3C+%5Cdfrac%7B1-%5Csqrt+5%7D2+%3C+1&#038;bg=ffffff&#038;fg=000&#038;s=0" alt="-1&lt; &#92;dfrac{1-&#92;sqrt 5}2 &lt; 1" title="-1&lt; &#92;dfrac{1-&#92;sqrt 5}2 &lt; 1" class="latex" />,</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>these terms tend to zero as <img src="//s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=n&#038;bg=ffffff&#038;fg=000&#038;s=0" alt="n" title="n" class="latex" /> tends to infinity, so are insignificant in comparison with the first terms. It follows that</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="//s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cfrac+%7BF_%7Bn%2B1%7D%7D%7BF_n%7D+%5Crightarrow+%5Cfrac%7B1%2B%5Csqrt+5%7D2+%5C+%5C+-+%5C+%5C+%5Ctextrm%7Bthe+Golden+Ratio%7D.+&#038;bg=ffffff&#038;fg=000&#038;s=0" alt="&#92;frac {F_{n+1}}{F_n} &#92;rightarrow &#92;frac{1+&#92;sqrt 5}2 &#92; &#92; - &#92; &#92; &#92;textrm{the Golden Ratio}. " title="&#92;frac {F_{n+1}}{F_n} &#92;rightarrow &#92;frac{1+&#92;sqrt 5}2 &#92; &#92; - &#92; &#92; &#92;textrm{the Golden Ratio}. " class="latex" /></p>
<p><a href="http://i1.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Untitled.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-11719" src="http://i1.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Untitled.png?resize=694%2C737" alt="Untitled" srcset="http://i1.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Untitled.png?resize=282%2C300 282w, http://i1.wp.com/www.mathemafrica.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Untitled.png?fit=694%2C737 694w" sizes="(max-width: 694px) 100vw, 694px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a>Check out the link between the golden spiral and the Fibonacci sequence <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_spiral">here</a>.</p>
<p>&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;&#8212;</p>
<p>Originally by John Webb</p>
